════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
KEY DIFFERENCES vs FixedExpert (from the previous log)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

FixedExpert (max_questions=2):
  - Asks EXACTLY 2 questions regardless of what the model knows
  - Abstention decision: pure rule (count questions), 0 LLM calls for this
  - Question generator sees: [system] + [user: answer prompt]
    (no reasoning context from the abstention step)

ScaleExpert + --rationale_generation:
  - Stopped after ONLY 1 question because score hit 4.0 (Somewhat Confident)
  - Abstention decision: 1 LLM call — model explains WHY it is uncertain
  - Question generator sees: [system] + [user: scale prompt] + [assistant: REASON+DECISION]
    (model's own reasoning feeds into what question it asks next)
  - Total calls: 6 vs 7 for FixedExpert in this case
    (saved 1 question turn by stopping earlier when confident)

